low barrier to entry
* being able to make a sound that doesn't hurt the ear
* simple process to take basic parts and put them together
* doesn’t take too long to go from vision of a sound to executing that vision
* beginner supportive ergonomics
* low physical demands
* repeatability - statelessness
* automatonism
	* little technique involved
	* information embedded in interface
	* all signals ae the same 
	* no way of breaking the system
	* ability to go beyond ‘expected’ usage